# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the values are
#   specific to the developer's system of choice.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different systems, you can let pipenv
#   keep it out of version control.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
#   and should be committed in a package or packaging project.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
